```python
_PARTIAL_PARSERS = {"setup.cfg", "Pipfile"}

def parse_manifest(content: str, path: str) -> list[DependencyCandidate]:
    filename = Path(path).name
    if filename in _PARSERS:
        if filename in _PARTIAL_PARSERS:
            print(
                f"  [warn] {path}: parsed as plain-text requirements "
                f"(INI/TOML structure ignored — coverage may be incomplete)",
                flush=True,
            )
        return _PARSERS[filename](content, path)
    if _REQUIREMENTS_PATTERN.match(filename):
        return _parse_requirements_txt(content, path)
    return []
```

Proper fix: implement `_parse_setup_cfg` using `configparser` to read `[options] install_requires` (and `[options.extras_require]` if desired), and `_parse_pipfile` using `tomllib`/`tomli` to read `[packages]` and `[dev-packages]`, then wire them into `_PARSERS`.

